					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Granted. But how easily do &quot;cheap new components&quot; compete latency-wise with good old SPI bit banging for the input and scanline rendering for the video output? The average video latency on an NES or Super NES with wired controllers and a CRT SDTV is 2 frames or 33 ms:<br /><br /><ul><li>Average 1/2 frame between button press and next controller read </li><li>Fixed 1 frame to process game logic, create a display list, and send it to the PPU </li><li>Average 1/2 frame from top of picture to player character's position </li></ul><br />Kev's Hi-Def NES adds 1 to 2 ms at the most, plus whatever lag the TV's scaler adds.<br /><br />How close do frame buffer based systems come?</div>

